<!-- Majordomo show_head format file -->
<h4 align=center>Personal Settings for $USER</h4>
<form method=POST action="$CGIURL">
  <input type=hidden name=domain value="$DOMAIN">
  <input type=hidden name=user value="$USER">
  <input type=hidden name=passw type=password value="$PASSWORD">
  <input size=36 name=extra>
  <input type=submit name=func value="alias">
  <input type=submit name=func value="changeaddr">
  <input type=submit name=func value="password-gen">
  <input type=submit name=func value="unregister"><br>

To add an $HELP:ALIAS (another e-mail address from which
you send messages), or to change addresses, type your new address into the box
and press the <b>alias</b> or <b>$HELP:CHANGEADDR</b> button.   
Majordomo may send a message to your new address asking for confirmation.

<p>
To change your $HELP:PASSWORD, leave the box empty and press the 
<b>password-gen</b> button.
Majordomo will create a new password and mail it to you. 
You will need to sign in again, using your new password, if
you wish to make any other changes to your subscriptions.

<p>
To $HELP:UNREGISTER, leave the box empty and press the <b>unregister</b>
button.  All of your subscriptions and aliases will be removed, and
your password will be invalidated.

<p>
To change settings, select the checkbox next to each list
you wish to change, choose the settings you want, then press 
the <b>set</b> button.  The settings are described at the bottom 
of this page.

<p>
To $HELP:UNSUBSCRIBE, select the checkbox next to each list
you wish to leave, then press the <b>unsubscribe</b> button.

<p>
  <input type=submit name=func value="set">
  <input type=submit name=func value="unsubscribe">

<table border>
<tr>
  <td><small>list</small>
  <td><small>delivery class</small>
  <td><small>$SETTINGS</small>

